---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Contact | classactionsettlementcalc.com';
const description = 'Contact the classactionsettlementcalc.com editorial team with corrections, feedback, or questions about class action settlement content.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Contact classactionsettlementcalc.com</h1>
  <p>The best way to reach us is by email at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>. We read every message and respond to substantive corrections and editorial feedback within five business days.</p>

  <h2>What We Can Help With</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Factual corrections:</strong> If you have identified an error in a procedural rule citation, a claims rate that is inconsistent with published data, or a calculator assumption that does not reflect documented settlement administration practice, share the specific claim, page URL, and source.</li>
    <li><strong>Methodology questions:</strong> The <a href="/methodology">methodology page</a> documents all calculator assumptions. For follow-up questions, email us.</li>
    <li><strong>Content suggestions:</strong> If a class action case type, procedural step, or practical topic is missing from the guides or FAQ, suggestions are welcome.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What We Cannot Help With</h2>
  <p>We cannot provide legal advice or case-specific analysis. We do not respond to questions like "How much will I get from [specific settlement]?", "Should I opt out of [specific case]?", or "Do I qualify for [specific settlement]?" For case-specific guidance, consult a class action attorney in your jurisdiction or contact the settlement administrator for the specific case directly. Settlement administrator contact information appears in the class notice for each settlement.</p>

  <h2>Advertising</h2>
  <p>classactionsettlementcalc.com is monetized exclusively through Google AdSense display advertising. We do not accept sponsored content, paid placements, or advertising arrangements outside the AdSense platform.</p>

  <p>Return to the <a href="/">calculator</a> or see the <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
